The paper deals with combinatorial structures, specifically directed graphs, and their properties related to covering and packing. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The Erd\H{o}s-P\'osa property is a well-known concept in graph theory, which suggests that certain classes of graphs have a common structure. Therefore, the paper is likely to be categorized under graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses results from previous research on graph minors, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper discusses the properties of tournaments, which are directed graphs with specific properties, and their relationship with other directed graphs. This falls under the scope of data structures (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
